Step 1 — Move the SDK to a clean location
Cut/paste the flutter folder from Downloads to C:\flutter using File Explorer. Avoid paths like Program Files (spaces cause issues).
Step 2 — Add Flutter to PATH
1. Press Windows key and search "Environment Variables"
2. Click "Edit the system environment variables"
3. Click "Environment Variables" button
4. Under User variables, click on Path → Edit
5. Click New and add:


   C:\flutter\bin
1. Click OK on all windows
Step 3 — Open a new terminal and verify:


bash
flutter --version
Step 4 — Enable web:


bash
flutter config --enable-web
Step 5 — Check setup:


bash
flutter doctor
 

macOS 
Step 1 — Move the SDK to a clean location

bash
mkdir ~/development
mv ~/Downloads/flutter ~/development/flutter

Step 2 — Add Flutter to PATH
bash
echo 'export PATH="$HOME/development/flutter/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.zshrc
source ~/.zshrc
Step 3 — Verify Flutter is found:


bash
flutter --version
Step 4 — Enable web:


bash
flutter config --enable-web
Step 5 — Check setup:


bash
flutter doctor

Or

brew --version
brew install --cask flutter
flutter config --enable-web
flutter doctor
